Said goodbye to my #GT3 recently. Bittersweet. It brought me nothing but joy, but, that was inherently part of the problem. At the end of the day, it was only ME who got anything out of it. 

My son LOVES cars and the fact that I couldn’t strap him into this (no back seats and the Clubsport buckets are not car seat friendly) meant that I had to stare at him in the rear view mirror every time I took it out for a drive. 😢 It also wasn’t the most comfortable car for my wife to squeeze in and out of either. At 5’2”, she could barely even see over the dash. 

If the last few months have taught me anything, it’s that life is short. Sure, do what makes you smile, buy the things you want, travel to wherever, but, what is it all worth if you can’t share these things, these moments, with the ones you love? 

Cars will always bring me joy, but now more than ever, I want to be able to share the hours in the garage wrenching on them, the Sunday drives to the local Cars & Coffee, and even school and soccer practice drop-offs with my son.😍

✌🏽 for now #Porsche #911 #GT3Clubsport…on to the next toy. 😉

TONIGHT on the season 3 premiere of #SupermanAndLois…”It’s been a long time, Lana” says Kyle. “S’all good though, because just like a rack of Kansas’ finest ribs…” Sarah, overhearing the convo utters under her breath, “no, no, don’t say it dad…” but it’s too late. “…baby, we’re back!” 😐 Superman is halfway across the globe but pauses his world saving for just a moment as his superhearing zeroes in on Kyle’s Dad joke and he’s like, “oh my God, that’s brilliant.” Later that day, there’s a party! 🎉 Clark takes this opportunity to try his hand at Kyle’s Dad joke on Lois… “ahhh, feels good to be back like a bunch of ribs, right baby?” Crickets. Meanwhile, on the Kent farmhouse porch, John Henry’s like, “with all do respect General, Hawaiian print is NOT the new camo.” Across the way, Jordan and Sarah are discussing Lane’s choice of wardrobe when all of the sudden, Jordan says, “speaking of fashion faux pas, someone needs to tell Beppo that paisley print and striped wrapping paper are NOT complimentary.” Chrissy feels everyone staring and immediately realizes why. She throws one box in a bush and awkwardly shoves the other to Jonathan who’s like, “umm, thanks?” Everyone watches as she scurries off, tripping over a garden hose. Later on that evening, Clark’s like, “look, babe…I’m sorry about the rib joke. I swear it wont happen again.” Lois, in tears is all, “I wish I could believe that Clark…I really do.” …or something like that. 🤔 Episode 301 written by our fearless leaders, @chipeyt & #BrentFletcher and directed by the incomparable, @cavanaghtom airs tonight at 8/7c on @thecw! 💥We’re so happy to be back…baby!!! 💙💛❤️

TONIGHT on #SupermanAndLois…Sarah and Natalie are grabbing lunch; “You ever wonder where our food comes from,” asks Nat. “Like for example, a quick search reveals that Vicky May sources these fries from a company called, Ore-Ida.” Sarah just stares. 

“Are they really discussing the origin of Vicky May’s French Fries,” says Jordan.” “Dude, are you really using your super hearing to eaves drop on a convo about potatoes” quips Jon. 

Meanwhile, Chrissy & Clark are laughing about a typo in this week’s Smallville Gazette while on their lunch break…”so I accidentally wrote FEET, instead of FEAT,” says Chrissy. 🤣 But something’s not sitting right with Lois. 

That afternoon, John Henry stops by Lana’s to check on her…over a glass of wine!? “Yeah, raising teenagers is…phew” says JH. “Like lately, Nat’s gone down a rabbit hole about food sources…did you know that Vicky May gets her fries from…” “Ore-Ida?” Lana interrupts. “Yeah, those are Kyle’s favorite.” Crickets. 

Later on, Chrissy meets up with Kyle to report on a cat rescue from Smallville’s tallest tree. She breaks the awkward silence… “Um…so how’s your Friday going? Cool, cool. Oh, speaking of Fries, get it…because, Fri-day…anyway, I overheard some random convo with Natalie Irons at lunch today…did you know that Vicky May gets her fries from…” “Ore-Ida?” Interrupts Kyle. “Yeah, those are my favorite.” “Ha…of course you knew that. Ore-Ida…what a funny name.” “The company is headquartered in Oregon, right next to the Idaho border…you know, Ore-Ida…? I thought everyone knew that, Chrissy.” 😐

That evening, back at the Gazette, Lois finally divulges what’s been eating at her. “She’s gunning for my job, Clark. Natalie Irons just uncovered Vicky May’s Fry source before I could even think to research it! Ugh, have I lost my touch?” Clark just stares, unsure how to answer. “Look Lois, if it’s any consolation, Kyle filled me in on that years ago.” Chrissy, overhearing this but in her own little world, mutters under her breath, “Mmm, Kyle…that man is a wealth of knowledge.” …or something like that. 🤔 

Episode 302 written by @katiealdrin and directed by the wonderful, @lil_henstridge, airs tonight at 8/7c on @thecw! 💥

TONIGHT on #SupermanAndLois…Chrissy confronts Kyle. “So, umm, I did a little digging into your past and, uh…tell me about ‘The Cush’...” “Oh, I’m not sure you’re ready for that,” Kyle smirks. 

Suddenly, Lana appears…”Kyle, don’t…”

But it’s too late. Word travels fast in Smallville and suddenly everyone is talking. Nat tells Matteo, “OMG, ‘The Cush’ is about to happen!” Matteo’s like, “WHAT!? My Dad’s gonna freak, he’s talked about ‘The Cush’ for as long as I can remember…I have to tell him!” 

Next thing you know, Bruno’s like, “look, Lois…I know we have our differences, but word on the street is, ‘The Cush’ is making a return! I need you and the Gazette to spread the word immediately!” 

Lois ASAPtually Google’s ‘The Cush Smallville’ and goes, OMG, I have to tell Clark!” Hits ELT. 

Whoosh!! Superman lands but in Clark garb… “Lois, what’s going on!?” “It’s The Cush…Bruno says it’s happening. Legend has it that he floats like a butterfly and has moves like Jagger. This entire wall is full of notes from random folks about how ‘The Cush’ brings joy to all that have bared witness. 😳

Back at the Smallville High V-Day dance…in April…‘The Cush’ appears, and boy oh boy, does Chrissy like it! Jaws drop. Hands go up. The whole place is lit! 

The next day, Jonathan runs into Kyle on the street and is like, “Hey Mr. Cushing! Look, I know my Dad’s got super powers and all, but that was like…AWESOME!! Can you teach me some moves?” …or something like that. 🤔 

Episode 305 is a banger written by #AndrewWong and directed by my man, @davidpaulramsey! Tune in tonight at 8/7c on @thecw! 💥🕺🏽
